<Class name="WsdlMethod" id="a2f02d92-f7f0-42bb-98ca-4903bc800532">
    <superclass name="Object"/>
    <transient/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>This class represents a webservice method.
It is equivalent to a method on a Provider or Consumer subclass
in Jade.

It has a reference to its endpoint (ie the Provider or Consumer
subclass to whom it belongs)

It has some user defined text (equivalent to the text property
on a method in Jade)

it has a name given to it in the wsdl - wsdlName
it has a unique name assigned to it by this application - uniqueName
The vast majority of the time the uniqueName will be identical to the wsdlName.
However, if a webservice contains multiple endpoints (ie multiple Provider
or Consumer subclasses) then more than one of those endpoints might define
a method of the same name. Because of the way the generated code works, we
need all methods to have a uniqueName within a wsdl rather than within an
endpoint. Hence if there is a name clash, we assign each a uniqueName.

parameters is a collection of WsdlParameters which represents the parameters
this method can take, like normal method parameters.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="richinternettoolset"/>
    <ImplicitInverseRef name="allBindings" id="5b3ce3e2-3224-4198-ac12-35dd8650fcf8">
        <memberTypeInverse/>
        <type name="ObjectArray"/>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
    <ExplicitInverseRef name="myEndpoint" id="567fd4e4-be60-424c-84c7-f9e2197e5f2d">
        <updateMode>automatic</updateMode>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="WsdlEndpoint"/>
        <Inverse name="WsdlEndpoint::methods"/>
    </ExplicitInverseRef>
    <ImplicitInverseRef name="parameters" id="fa51c298-dc60-4b3d-bc14-b679f733e6a1">
        <memberTypeInverse/>
        <type name="WParamArray"/>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
    <PrimAttribute name="text" id="201d21f9-1f12-4565-8842-82240618fb82">
        <type name="String"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="uniqueName" id="d981e64d-175a-42ab-b5e0-b4377f9b2cbb">
        <type name="String"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="wsdlName" id="a63b89bc-f6f3-4d59-bc3a-9e4286743a39">
        <length>101</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
</Class>
